{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MEpRazXuNBPc9nrEcJBMBh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me understand the current setup:\n\n1. **Elasticsearch (source)**: 3-node StatefulSet, ES 8.11.1, HTTPS with TLS certs, security enabled (elastic/elasticpass)\n2. **Monitoring cluster**: Single-node deployment, ES 7.17.9, HTTP (no TLS), no security\n3. ES logs go to **stdout** only (Console appenders in log4j2.properties)\n4. The only file-based logs are GC logs at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/logs/`\n\n**Plan:**\nI need to update the log4j2.properties to write server logs to disk, then create ConfigMaps for the logging and beat configurations. After that, I'll patch the StatefulSet to mount an emptyDir volume for logs, inject the custom log4j2 config, and add metricbeat and filebeat sidecars to collect and forward the metrics and logs to the monitoring cluster. Writing appender configuration... CS JSON log events to the monitoring cluster. I'll skip the Filebeat elasticsearch module for now and keep it simple with a basic log input. The log4j2.properties ConfigMap needs to mount as a single file using `subPath` to override just that specific file in the config directory. My plan is to create three ConfigMaps for the log4j2 configuration, metricbeat, and filebeat, then patch the StatefulSet to add volumes for the logs directory and both monitoring tool configurations.\n\nNow I'm writing out the YAML files. I'm considering version compatibility between metricbeat 7.17.9 and Elasticsearch 8.11.1 — the standard REST APIs should work fine since they're backward compatible and the elastic user has superuser privileges.\n\nOne thing I need to verify is the SSL configuration for metricbeat. I'll mount the CA certificate from the `es-http-tls` secret at `/etc/ssl/elasticsearch/ca.crt` so metricbeat can validate the Elasticsearch TLS certificate.\n\nFor the verification mode, I should use `certificate` rather than `none` since the CA from the secret should properly validate the server certificate, even though the hostname won't match exactly.\n\nNow I'm ready to write out the complete implementation, starting with the log4j2.properties configuration where I need to preserve all the existing appenders while making the necessary adjustments. Finishing the file appender configuration with ECS JSON layout, time-based rolling policies that trigger daily, and a default rollover strategy, then updating the root logger to reference both the console and file appenders.\n\nI need to be careful with the YAML formatting for the ConfigMap since the properties file contains special characters like backslashes in the audit log patterns, so I'll use a literal block scalar to preserve the formatting exactly. Once the volume mounts at the logs directory, Elasticsearch will create the server log file there, and the RollingFile appender will handle it automatically—the directory starts empty but the JVM and ES will write their logs as they start up.\n\nNow I'm writing out all the YAML configuration. For metricbeat, I need to use the `--strict.perms=false` flag since ConfigMaps mount with default permissions that don't match what metricbeat expects for its config files. The elasticsearch module with xpack enabled will collect cluster stats, node stats, index stats, and shard stats, writing them to the monitoring indices.\n\nI'm deciding whether to disable template setup entirely with `setup.template.enabled: false` to let Elasticsearch handle dynamic mappings instead, which simplifies the configuration since the monitoring cluster is the same version as metricbeat.\n\nNow I need to verify that metricbeat can reach `https://localhost:9200` from the sidecar container—since they share the network namespace, localhost will correctly point to the Elasticsearch container's port. The HTTPS requirement means I'll need to configure metricbeat to use the proper SSL settings to connect securely.\n\nThe `es-http-tls` secret provides the CA certificate that metricbeat needs to verify the server's identity, so I'll mount that secret and reference the CA certificate in the metricbeat configuration.\n\nNow I'm ready to write out the full implementation. I'll create everything in a single YAML file and apply it with kubectl. For the log4j2.properties configuration, I need to add a file appender section alongside the existing console appender, then update the root logger to include both appenders.\n\nWriting the kubectl resources...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7988,"cache_read_input_tokens":46515,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7988},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34b30af3-95da-40fc-b631-05bf5531cd48","uuid":"5c4cde56-13b7-4f42-889b-105e18c95008","request_id":"req_011CcMbK8cdyMi7n5ZGXMvKK"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MEpRazXuNBPc9nrEcJBMBh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture:\n- ES logs go to **stdout only** (Console appenders) — no log files except GC logs\n- I need to add a RollingFile appender to log4j2.properties so Filebeat can read them from a shared emptyDir\n- Metricbeat connects to `https://localhost:9200` with the CA cert from the `es-http-tls` secret\n- Monitoring cluster at `monitoring-es-http.monitoring:9200` has no auth\n\nI'll create the 3 ConfigMaps (log4j2, metricbeat, filebeat) and patch the StatefulSet to add the sidecars and shared log volume."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7988,"cache_read_input_tokens":46515,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7988},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34b30af3-95da-40fc-b631-05bf5531cd48","uuid":"6bd881bb-78df-4308-8872-a0a4cb1cf977","request_id":"req_011CcMbK8cdyMi7n5ZGXMvKK"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MEpRazXuNBPc9nrEcJBMBh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01W1RpuAZzn2YoqR8uGAiHbJ","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /tmp/monitoring-configmaps.yaml << 'YAML'\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: es-log4j2-config\n  namespace: elasticsearch\ndata:\n  log4j2.properties: |\n    status = error\n\n    ######## Server JSON ############################\n    appender.rolling.type = Console\n    appender.rolling.name = rolling\n    appender.rolling.layout.type = ECSJsonLayout\n    appender.rolling.layout.dataset = elasticsearch.server\n\n    ######## Server JSON File #######################\n    appender.rolling_file.type = RollingFile\n    appender.rolling_file.name = rolling_file\n    appender.rolling_file.fileName = ${sys:es.logs.base_path}/${sys:es.logs.cluster_name}_server.json\n    appender.rolling_file.filePattern = ${sys:es.logs.base_path}/${sys:es.logs.cluster_name}_server-%d{yyyy-MM-dd}.json.gz\n    appender.rolling_file.layout.type = ECSJsonLayout\n    appender.rolling_file.layout.dataset = elasticsearch.server\n    appender.rolling_file.policies.type = Policies\n    appender.rolling_file.policies.time.type = TimeBasedTriggeringPolicy\n    appender.rolling_file.policies.time.interval = 1\n    appender.rolling_file.policies.time.modulate = true\n    appender.rolling_file.strategy.type = DefaultRolloverStrategy\n    appender.rolling_file.strategy.fileIndex = nomax\n\n    ################################################\n\n    rootLogger.level = info\n    rootLogger.appenderRef.rolling.ref = rolling\n    rootLogger.appenderRef.rolling_file.ref = rolling_file\n\n    ######## Deprecation JSON #######################\n    appender.deprecation_rolling.type = Console\n    appender.deprecation_rolling.name = deprecation_rolling\n    appender.deprecation_rolling.layout.type = ECSJsonLayout\n    appender.deprecation_rolling.layout.dataset = deprecation.elasticsearch\n    appender.deprecation_rolling.filter.rate_limit.type = RateLimitingFilter\n\n    appender.header_warning.type = HeaderWarningAppender\n    appender.header_warning.name = header_warning\n    #################################################\n\n    logger.deprecation.name = org.elasticsearch.deprecation\n    logger.deprecation.level = WARN\n    logger.deprecation.appenderRef.deprecation_rolling.ref = deprecation_rolling\n    logger.deprecation.appenderRef.header_warning.ref = header_warning\n    logger.deprecation.additivity = false\n\n    ######## Search slowlog JSON ####################\n    appender.index_search_slowlog_rolling.type = Console\n    appender.index_search_slowlog_rolling.name = index_search_slowlog_rolling\n    appender.index_search_slowlog_rolling.layout.type = ECSJsonLayout\n    appender.index_search_slowlog_rolling.layout.dataset = elasticsearch.index_search_slowlog\n\n    logger.index_search_slowlog_rolling.name = index.search.slowlog\n    logger.index_search_slowlog_rolling.level = trace\n    logger.index_search_slowlog_rolling.appenderRef.index_search_slowlog_rolling.ref = index_search_slowlog_rolling\n    logger.index_search_slowlog_rolling.additivity = false\n\n    ######## Indexing slowlog JSON ##################\n    appender.index_indexing_slowlog_rolling.type = Console\n    appender.index_indexing_slowlog_rolling.name = index_indexing_slowlog_rolling\n    appender.index_indexing_slowlog_rolling.layout.type = ECSJsonLayout\n    appender.index_indexing_slowlog_rolling.layout.dataset = elasticsearch.index_indexing_slowlog\n\n    logger.index_indexing_slowlog.name = index.indexing.slowlog.index\n    logger.index_indexing_slowlog.level = trace\n    logger.index_indexing_slowlog.appenderRef.index_indexing_slowlog_rolling.ref = index_indexing_slowlog_rolling\n    logger.index_indexing_slowlog.additivity = false\n\n    logger.org_apache_pdfbox.name = org.apache.pdfbox\n    logger.org_apache_pdfbox.level = off\n    logger.org_apache_poi.name = org.apache.poi\n    logger.org_apache_poi.level = off\n    logger.org_apache_fontbox.name = org.apache.fontbox\n    logger.org_apache_fontbox.level = off\n    logger.org_apache_xmlbeans.name = org.apache.xmlbeans\n    logger.org_apache_xmlbeans.level = off\n    logger.com_amazonaws.name = com.amazonaws\n    logger.com_amazonaws.level = warn\n    logger.com_amazonaws_jmx_SdkMBeanRegistrySupport.name = com.amazonaws.jmx.SdkMBeanRegistrySupport\n    logger.com_amazonaws_jmx_SdkMBeanRegistrySupport.level = error\n    logger.com_amazonaws_metrics_AwsSdkMetrics.name = com.amazonaws.metrics.AwsSdkMetrics\n    logger.com_amazonaws_metrics_AwsSdkMetrics.level = error\n    logger.com_amazonaws_auth_profile_internal_BasicProfileConfigFileLoader.name = com.amazonaws.auth.profile.internal.BasicProfileConfigFileLoader\n    logger.com_amazonaws_auth_profile_internal_BasicProfileConfigFileLoader.level = error\n    logger.com_amazonaws_services_s3_internal_UseArnRegionResolver.name = com.amazonaws.services.s3.internal.UseArnRegionResolver\n    logger.com_amazonaws_services_s3_internal_UseArnRegionResolver.level = error\n\n    logger.xpack_security_audit_logfile.name = org.elasticsearch.xpack.security.audit.logfile.LoggingAuditTrail\n    logger.xpack_security_audit_logfile.level = info\n    logger.xpack_security_audit_logfile.additivity = false\n\n    logger.xmlsig.name = org.apache.xml.security.signature.XMLSignature\n    logger.xmlsig.level = error\n    logger.samlxml_decrypt.name = org.opensaml.xmlsec.encryption.support.Decrypter\n    logger.samlxml_decrypt.level = fatal\n    logger.saml2_decrypt.name = org.opensaml.saml.saml2.encryption.Decrypter\n    logger.saml2_decrypt.level = fatal\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: metricbeat-config\n  namespace: elasticsearch\ndata:\n  metricbeat.yml: |\n    metricbeat.modules:\n    - module: elasticsearch\n      xpack.enabled: true\n      period: 10s\n      hosts: [\"https://localhos