{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019uXcqfnej48jb7DY44n2bQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to restart the Filebeat sidecars to pick up the new config. In Kubernetes, updating a ConfigMap doesn't automatically restart the pods. I need to either:\n1. Delete and recreate the pods (disrupts the ES cluster temporarily)\n2. Trigger a rolling restart of the StatefulSet\n\nActually, in Kubernetes, ConfigMap changes are eventually propagated to the mounted volumes (there's a kubelet sync period, typically 60s). So if I wait, the Filebeat containers should pick up the new config after ~60 seconds (configmap sync period). But the running filebeat process won't automatically reload the config unless it's configured to do so.\nFilebeat 7.17 supports hot-reload for modules with `reload.enabled: true`, but the main config file still requires a restart. The safest approach would be a rolling restart of the StatefulSet, though that would briefly impact cluster health. I could delete the Filebeat pods directly to restart just those containers, but that would also momentarily restart the ES container since they're in the same pod. Alternatively, I could wait for the ConfigMap to propagate and then exec into the pod to verify the changes.\n\nThe cleanest option is using `kubectl rollout restart` on the StatefulSet to do a rolling restart one pod at a time, which is acceptable for a 3-node cluster. But I should first verify whether this is even necessary—the Filebeat index shows zero documents with the mapper_parsing exception, so if I fix the config and let it propagate, I still need Filebeat to actually reload and pick up those changes. I can't restart just the filebeat container without restarting the entire pod, which means ES restarts too. That's fine for a 3-node cluster, but I'm wondering if there's a simpler way—maybe I could send a signal to filebeat directly to reload its config. Let me check if filebeat supports SIGHUP for hot-reloading the main configuration file.\n\nActually, filebeat only supports hot-reload for specific input configs when `reload.enabled: true` is set. The main config requires a full restart. So I'll trigger a rolling restart of the statefulset to bring the pods back up one at a time.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":692,"cache_read_input_tokens":71661,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":692},"output_tokens":35,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"34b30af3-95da-40fc-b631-05bf5531cd48","uuid":"07ec322c-90ac-490a-8f72-d86c4afa89df","request_id":"req_011CcMbujdWH6RsZG8jbQwVR"}
